  "title": "Head of HSE (Shipyard)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description:</strong></p><p><p><ul><li>Enforce full compliance with all Health, Safety, and Environmental (HSE) policies, standards, and statutory requirements across all fabrication facilities.</li><li>Lead the effective rollout and execution of project-specific HSE Management Plans.</li><li>Organize and manage the deployment of qualified safety personnel to ensure adequate HSE coverage and oversight during project activities.</li><li>Provide support during project tender and bidding stages by performing gap assessments between project HSE requirements and existing yard HSE systems to identify key risks.</li><li>Promote and lead proactive safety programs and behavioral-based initiatives to strengthen a positive HSE culture and drive continuous improvement across the worksite.</li><li>Work closely with Production and Operations teams to ensure HSE practices are fully integrated into daily operations.</li><li>Monitor, evaluate, and report on yard and project HSE performance data, identifying leading indicators and implementing corrective and preventive actions.</li></ul></p></p><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><p><p><ul><li>Diploma/ Bachelor’s Degree in Engineering or any related fields.</li><li>Minimum 5 years of working experience as HSE Manager.</li><li>Excellent communication and presentation skills</li></ul></p></p><p>Interested applicants for the above advertised position(s), please kindly email an updated copy of your resume to: <strong>gs1@talenttradersg.com;</strong></p><p><br /></p><p>EA License No.: 13C6305</p><p>Registration No.: R23117856 CHOE KIN MUN</p><p><br /></p><p>For candidate who applied for the advertised position is deemed to have consented to us that we may collect, use or disclose your personal information for purpose in connection with the services provided by us.</p>",
